attributes.name: sequenceNr
attributes.label: Sequence number
attributes.description: Number that defines order of attributes in a entity

attributes.name: mappedBy
attributes.label: Mapped by
attributes.description: Attribute in the referenced entity that owns the relationship of a onetomany attribute

attributes.name: orderBy
attributes.label: Order by
attributes.description: Order expression that defines entity collection order of a onetomany attribute (e.g. "attr0", "attr0,ASC", "attr0,DESC" or "attr0,ASC;attr1,DESC"

attributes.name: expression
attributes.label: Expression
attributes.description: Computed value expression in Magma JavaScript

refEntity.name: sys_md_Tag
refEntity.label: Tag
refEntity.description: Semantic tags that can be applied to entities, attributes and other data

items.name: #CHROM
items.description: The chromosome on which the variant is observed

items.name: POS
items.description: The position on the chromosome which the variant is observed

items.name: CIEND
items.description: Confidence interval around END for imprecise variants

items.name: CIPOS
items.description: Confidence interval around POS for imprecise variants

items.name: MEINFO
items.description: Mobile element info of the form NAME,START,END<POLARITY; If there is only 5' OR 3' support for this call, will be NULL NULL for START and END

items.name: MEND
items.description: Mitochondrial end coordinate of inserted sequence

items.name: MSTART
items.description: Mitochondrial start coordinate of inserted sequence

items.name: SVLEN
items.description: Difference in length between REF and ALT alleles

items.name: TSD
items.description: Precise Target Site Duplication for bases, if unknown, value will be NULL

items.name: AC
items.description: Total number of alternate alleles in called genotypes

items.name: AF
items.description: Estimated allele frequency in the range (0,1)

items.name: AN
items.description: Total number of alleles in called genotypes

items.name: EAS_AF
items.description: Allele frequency in the EAS populations calculated from AC and AN, in the range (0,1)

items.name: EUR_AF
items.description: Allele frequency in the EUR populations calculated from AC and AN, in the range (0,1)

items.name: AFR_AF
items.description: Allele frequency in the AFR populations calculated from AC and AN, in the range (0,1)

items.name: AMR_AF
items.description: Allele frequency in the AMR populations calculated from AC and AN, in the range (0,1)

items.name: SAS_AF
items.description: Allele frequency in the SAS populations calculated from AC and AN, in the range (0,1)

items.name: AA
items.description: Ancestral Allele. Format: AA|REF|ALT|IndelType. AA: Ancestral allele, REF:Reference Allele, ALT:Alternate Allele, IndelType:Type of Indel (REF, ALT and IndelType are only defined for indels)
